}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4747"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "neurofilament light", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.994188666343689, "span": {"begin": 917, "end": 936}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4747"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "NFL", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.990795373916626, "span": {"begin": 938, "end": 941}}, {"id": ["mim:118200", "mesh:D002607"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999997615814209, "span": {"begin": 973, "end": 1000}}, {"id": ["mesh:D010523"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "peripheral neuropathy", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999873042106628, "span": {"begin": 1004, "end": 1025}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Neuronal cultures", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.8995408415794373, "span": {"begin": 1027, "end": 1044}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:161742"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "NFL mutants", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9862216711044312, "span": {"begin": 1048, "end": 1059}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4747"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "mutant NFL protein", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9935643076896667, "span": {"begin": 1109, "end": 1127}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009410"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "degeneration of neurites", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999505877494812, "span": {"begin": 1151, "end": 1175}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009422"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "neuropathy", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999277591705322, "span": {"begin": 1229, "end": 1239}}, {"id": ["mim:118200", "mesh:D002607"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "CMT", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999960660934448, "span": {"begin": 1255, "end": 1258}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "patients", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9858903884887695, "span": {"begin": 1259, "end": 1267}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:4747"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "NFL mutations", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9135769605636597, "span": {"begin": 1273, "end": 1286}}], "text": "- Mutated KIF1B was shown to lose motor activity and did not move towards the plus end of microtubules. [2] A loss of function in motor proteins leads to disruption of transport along microtubules and therefore also of axonal transport. As this mutation of KIF1B was shown to be linked to CMT2A [2], a peripheral neuropathy, a direct link between axonal transport defects and peripheral neuropathy can be created.  - Transport of the synaptic vesicle precursor synaptotagmin was shown to be decreased in mice with a knockout of the KIF1A motor protein. These mice also exhibited axonal degeneration and showed motor and sensory disturbances. [3]  - Neuropathy was induced in cats by administration of acrylamide. Cats exhibited neuropathic symptoms like foot drop and also axonal degeneration was documented. Axonal transport was proven to be disturbed in acrylamide-neuropathic cats. [4]  - Several mutations in the neurofilament light (NFL) gene have been shown to cause Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease, a peripheral neuropathy. Neuronal cultures of NFL mutants exhibited reduced axonal transport. Furthermore, mutant NFL protein overexpression lead to degeneration of neurites. This observation points to a potential mechanism of neuropathy development in CMT patients with NFL mutations. [5]", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:15:01 +0000 2026"}